text:
Deepak RJ
I write about medical AI for clinicians, with a focus on actualising AI for psychiatry - the only medical specialty with worsening outcomes.
As a medical student, AI researcher, and long-term insight meditator, I track how technology is reshaping healthcare while exploring deeper questions about attention, identity, computational psychiatry and what it means to understand minds. I work at the tight-knit MMTL.
Twitter | LinkedIn | GitHub


Current Projects


Ambi

Rethinking the doctor-patient relationship in an agent-run clinic.

Nexus

Clinicians need to learn about AI. We aim to create the nexus for all things medical AI, from education to research news.

Clarity

Seed funded by MIME. Built a RAG system for centralised clinical decision support.

Chute

Automating clinical registry entry for clinicians using LLMs.

GAMSnack

AI-powered education platform aiming to bring the cost of effective 1-on-1 tutoring down to pennies.





